Clerk: EZ. Defendant Joseph Robert Pischke in court, in custody.  Attorney Daryl W Laatsch in court for Joseph Robert Pischke.  Prosecuting attorney Mark David Bensen in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Counsel's first appearance after substitution and prior counsel had engaged an expert.
Hearing scheduled for November 2, 2022 at 09:45 am.
$10,000 cash bond amended to $5,000 cash bond; No contact with any females under age 18; no contact with KGS or KGS's residence; Defendant subject to GPD monitoring device

Clerk: EZ. Prosecuting attorney Stephanie L Hanson in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Joseph Robert Pischke in court, in custody.  Attorney Edgar A Beltran in court for Joseph Robert Pischke.  Defendant waives reading of the Information.  Not guilty plea entered.  Atty. Beltran does not believe the case will proceed to trial and request adjournment to hire an expert.  Atty. Beltran moves for bond amendment to $1,000.00 cash bond and makes argument.  State objects to bond modification and bakes argument.  Further argument by Atty. Beltran and State.  Court amends cash bond to $5,000.00 cash bond.
Hearing scheduled for September 19, 2022 at 09:45 am.

Clerk: EZ. Prosecuting attorney Elizabeth A Longo in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Joseph Robert Pischke in court, in custody.  Attorney Edgar A Beltran in court for Joseph Robert Pischke. Preliminary hearing waived.  Court binds defendant over for trial and State shall file an Information.  Atty. Beltran requests bond modification.  State opposes bond modification.  Court denies bond modification and counsel can file formal motion to have bond revisited.
Arraignment scheduled for August 3, 2022 at 08:15 am.
No contact with K.G.S. or K.G.S.'s residence. No contact with any females under age of 18 years.

Prosecuting Attorney Allison E. Cogbill in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant appears in person in custody from the Washington County Jail and by Atty. Wilfred de Junco.  Defendant given complaint, advised of charges, penalties and rights, and probable cause found.  Atty. de Junco did not have an opportunity to interview defendant today.  Defendant referred to State Public Defender.  Argument on bond.  State requests $10,000 cash bond.  Defendant is on a PO hold. Preliminary hearing time limits waived.  Adjourned for position on preliminary hearing and to appear with counsel.
